.:.... rELEASE nOTES

L.A.'s Tiptop Audio modular synth
manufacturers flash their product via trax
from Blawan, Surgeon, KiNK, Richard Devine,
John Tejada and more. Spread over two discs,
you'll find some surprisingly pedestrian gear
from most, including John Tejada and
Drumcell's Phase VI duo and the big techno
lads like Surgeon or Blawan. It's left to
Richard Devine, who probably has more
experience with modular systems than the rest
put together, to give the standout moment in
'CR Hex Mutant''s febrile scramble of sparks
and plonging, arrhythmic pulses, and also
Joseph Fraioli, whose  -alike 'Circadian
Rhythms' put the by-numbers house and techno
pieces in sharp relief.
